{'book': {'publisher': 'Alamah', 'synopsis': "Product Description      <br/>Feng shui is the ancient Chinese art of life-space design. It teaches that our surroundings have a tremendous subconscious impact on our health, attitude, relationships, and success. This beautifully illustrated books shows you how.<br/>Blurb in Spanish:Feng Shui. La armonía entre tu espacio interior y el medio que te rodea <br/>En esta guía encontrarás los elementos necesarios para atraer la buena fortuna, mejorar tus relaciones personales y tener una carrera profesional exitosa por medio del feng sui, el antiguo arte chino del diseño de los espacios vitales. La experta Zaihong Shen te brinda claras y detalladas instrucciones para aplicar los principios fundamentales a todos los ambientes que te rodean. Con esta obra obtendrás: <br/>-el estímulo del buen ch'i, la fuerza vital universal, con sencillos consejos y prácticas que pronto rendirán los frutos deseados; <br/>-la correcta disposición de los elementos más importantes como puertas, ventanas, escaleras y dormitorios; <br/>-sugerencias decorativas que, además de belleza, te brindarán buenos auspicios, como recomendaciones sobre el color adecuado para habitaciones específicas, el lugar idóneo para colocar plantas, espejos y muchas ideas más; <br/>-soluciones para equilibrar el yin (principio femenino) con el yang (principio masculino), utilizando materiales que brindan una sensación de armonía en cada habitación; <br/>-maravillosas fotografías en color y útiles planos que ilustran los conceptos fundamentales del feng sui.<br/>      From Publishers Weekly      <br/>A feng shui teacher trained in China, Shen currently directs an institute dedicated to the cultural exchange between East and West. Feng shui is an ancient Chinese practice based on the idea that every object projects energy into its surroundings. Considered one of the nine healing arts of Taoism, it empha- sizes maximizing positive energy through the strategic placement of objects. In the first section of the book, Shen identifies the origins of this practice in Taoism, Buddhism, and Confucianism. He then describes the two main schools of feng shuithe School of the Form and the School of the Compassand applies their teachings to the strategic placement of doors, furniture, buildings, houses, and gardens. In the third section, Shen does the same for business places. The illustrations are the most outstanding quality of this book, featuring ancient Chinese paintings, modern drawings, charts, graphs, and excellent color photography. Together with the glossary, they greatly contribute to the understanding of a complicated topic. This accurate and easy-to-read translation is recommended for public libraries and bookstores with New Age collections.Sonia Merubia, Univ. of Texas Lib., Austin<br/>Copyright 2002 Reed Business Information, Inc.", 'language': 'es', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/86/52/9789681908652.jpg', 'title_long': 'Feng Shui (Spanish Edition)', 'dimensions': 'Height: 9 Inches, Length: 7 Inches, Weight: 1.33 Pounds, Width: 0.5 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 7}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.5}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.33}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 9}}, 'pages': 192, 'date_published': '2001', 'subjects': ['Self-Help', 'Stress Management', 'Health, Fitness & Dieting', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'New Age & Spirituality', 'Other Eastern Religions & Sacred Texts', 'Feng Shui'], 'authors': ['Zaihong Shen'], 'title': 'Feng Shui (Spanish Edition)', 'isbn13': '9789681908652', 'msrp': 1.99, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '9681908651', 'isbn10': '9681908651'}}